<p>SCP was my life for a good chunk of my high-school and college years. First the writing community, then the RP community, and then long days on Skype with the guys playing on steam. SCP wasn't just a past time, it fundamentally changed who I am today. My sense of humor. My storytelling ability. My leadership skills. My tolerance for scary fucking shit. The ability to fix any router in 5 minutes because I'm GMING DAMNIT! All would be lacking if I didn't have this great community encouraging me all the way.</p>
<p>There were trying moments, times when I had to just get up from my computer and just sit alone for a while. Sometimes I still can't forgive myself for how things happened, all the signs I missed and the people that were hurt. For all my failures, as a bystander, GM, writer, and Salmanderp I am truly sorry.</p>
<p>But these too were learning experiences, and I could not have gotten through them without the wonderful people I was surrounded by. You people are truly the greatest, and I hope you remain as a bastion of light in this dark internet. SCP is a sanctuary for the disconnected and a shield for the passionate. I hope it continues for many happy years.</p>
<p>My things I leave to Roget too delegate, as he knows how to reach me &amp; I trust his judgment. However, I request that my articles be left open to open moderation, without the need to await my consultation. I might return and revert it, but I can't guarantee any article maintenance (so please don't PM me, you'll be wasting your time. Just ask a mod).</p>
<p>As for my sandbox, I'm not sure what to do. I suppose I'll make it open to use by anybody, inside and outside SCP (Just remember that everything in my sandboxes is posted under the Wikidot CC license). This includes all my non-published SCP works, especially all work in SCP RPs. I would be thrilled to see somebody recycle that material.</p>
<p>The exception to this is The Ghost Sign, which is part of a broader character I use in on-stage acts, and does not directly originate from SCP.</p>
<p>pls pm me 4 gdby cnt w8 bby</p>

							</div>

								
					
